  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat. Add the chicken thighs and cook until browned on both sides, about 5 minutes.",
    "Remove the chicken from the pot and set aside.",
    "Add the onion to the pot and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic and ginger to the pot and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the herbes-de-provence, cumin, and paprika to the pot and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the tomatoes, chicken broth, salt, and black pepper to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Return the chicken to the pot and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, about 30 minutes.",
    "Stir in the chopped parsley and serve the stew hot with toasted bread."
